  "prompt_text": "A coworker is visibly upset after receiving harsh criticism in a meeting. How do you approach them?",
  "response_text": "Approach your coworker in a private and calm setting. Begin by expressing empathy and understanding for their feelings, acknowledging the criticism they received in the meeting.\n\n\"Hey [Coworker's Name], I noticed you seemed upset after the meeting. I wanted to check in and see if you're okay. I understand that receiving criticism can be tough, and I'm here to support you.\"\n\nNext, try to help them process the feedback by focusing on the constructive aspects and potential learning opportunities.\n\n\"I wanted to discuss the feedback you received. While it may have been harsh, there might be some valuable insights in there. Let's take a look at the specific points and see if we can identify areas for improvement or new ways to approach your work.\"\n\nEncourage them to share their thoughts and feelings about the criticism, and offer your perspective if appropriate.\n\n\"What do you think about the feedback you received? I'd love to hear your thoughts and help you brainstorm some strategies for addressing the concerns raised.\"\n\nFinally, reassure them that everyone makes mistakes and that it's an opportunity for growth.\n\n\"Remember, it's okay to make mistakes. We all do. The important thing is to learn from them and grow as professionals. I believe in your abilities, and I'm confident that you'll come out of this stronger.\"\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 9\nV (Verbal Fluency): 8\nG (Goal Directedness): 9\nP (Pattern Recognition): 8\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 7\nQ (Query Interpretation): 9\nC (Contextual Awareness): 9\nY (Affective Modeling): 8\nF (Flexibility): 8\nD (Depth of Processing): 8\n---END RATINGS---",
